descp2: A single value compatible with `dtype` or an iterable of values compatible with `dtype` which the column takes on during`tf.Example` parsing if data is missing. A default value of `None` will cause `tf.io.parse_example` to fail if an example does not contain this column. If a single value is provided, the same value will be applied as the default value for every item. If an iterable of values is provided, the shape of the `default_value` should be equal to the given `shape`.
